# GitHub Actions Conventions

- Set default permissions to `read-all` at the workflow level
- Use concurrency groups with `cancel-in-progress: true` to avoid redundant runs
- Pin all third-party actions by full commit SHA, not tags (e.g. `uses: actions/checkout@<sha> # v6.0.2`)
- Include the version as an inline comment after the SHA for readability
- Always include `step-security/harden-runner` as the first step in every job with `egress-policy: audit`
- Use `continue-on-error: true` for steps that test expected failures (disallowed pulls/builds)
- Validate expected outcomes explicitly in a subsequent step, failing the job if assertions don't hold
